creator: Various
description:
LibriVox recording of Short Poetry Collection 155 by Various.
Read in English by Craig Campbell; Tomas Peter; Newgatenovelist; Shakira Searle; Bruce Kachuk; Sonia; Kalynda; VfkaBT; Ross Klatte; Tony Addison; Son of the Exiles; Chris; Marissa Parker; Marwa Khalouf; Algy Pug; dutchbjork
This is a collection of the following 31 poems read by LibriVox volunteers for April 2016:
After the Small Pox, by Mary Jones April Love, by Ernest Dowson April Midnight, by Arthur Symons Azure and Gold, by Amy Lowell But Not to Me, by Sara Teasdale The House with Nobody in It, by Joyce Kilmer I Love You, by Sara Teasdale The Lady of Shalott, by Alfred, Lord Tennyson Lines on a Little Bird, by Sir John Carr Main Street, by Joyce Kilmer The Maldive Shark, by Herman Melville Memorial Day, by Joyce Kilmer The Music Lesson, by Mathilde Blind Night, by William Blake The Pleiades, by Arthur Adams The Power of Fancy, by Philip Freneau Socrates, by Frederick William Faber Song of Marion's Men, by William Cullen Bryant Sonnet 116, by William Shakespeare Sonnet 30, by William Shakespeare Sonnet 73, by William Shakespeare Sonnet IV, by Francesco Petrarca Spring's Bedfellow, by William Morris Stand By The Engines, by Henry Lawson Stars, by Sara Teasdale Surrender, by Ella Wheeler Wilcox Three and One, by Ella Wheeler Wilcox To One in Paradise, by Edgar Allan Poe We are Seven, by William Wordsworth Windflower Leaf, by Carl Sandburg The Wood-pile, by Robert Frost For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
